According to publisher HarperCollins, 82-year-old actor Clint Eastwood’s new autobiography, , will be released this October, just in time for the holiday book-buying season.“When you write…it’s just that so, these people are all in our lives, all of us, and he’s—but you know about—I remember 50 years ago,” reads an excerpt from a chapter titled “You See The Past And It Doesn’t Hurt, I Don’t Know.” “They were saying, but I thought—people in your own life were something to be thought about—and they were saying that back then, and even now, and I just thought, this is great.”“My mom was crying, I was crying, and my dad—and I haven’t…but I thought, yeah, and  was then,” the excerpt continues.